This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on using intrinsic rewards to improve reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper also involves training a policy to perform computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of intrinsic motivation and affective rewards also suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves training a reward function, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of positive affect on learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
